PyGlang - Translate text with the 'Google AJAX Language API'

By David Keegan <keegan3d@gmail.com>
With contributions from John Burnett

http://bitbucket.org/keegan3d/pyglang

License
~~~~~~~

PyGlang is distributed under the MIT license, see the LICENSE file for more information.

Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~

This is a standard Python distutils distribution. To install the
package, run the following command as an administrative user:

    python setup.py install


How to say 'Hello'
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

import PyGlang

for language in PyGlang.GetLanguages().iterkeys():
    try:
        print language, PyGlang.Translate('Hello', fromLang='English', toLang=language)
     except PyGlang.TranslationError:
        print ''